# Master reproducibility notebook

This notebook provides an end-to-end overview of the reproducible workflow used in the manuscript.

## Workflow steps
1. Load input datasets from `data_input/`
2. Preprocess monthly groundwater-level and precipitation time series
3. Compute SPI and SGI indices
4. Derive drought-event metrics (severity, duration, recovery, propagation)
5. Construct DIPI components and final DIPI maps
6. Export figure source data to `figure_source_data/`

## Execution
Run the notebooks in the following order:

1. `../notebooks/01_preprocessing_SPI_SGI.ipynb`
2. `../notebooks/02_event_metrics.ipynb`
3. `../notebooks/03_DIPI_construction.ipynb`
4. `../notebooks/04_figures_main_text.ipynb`

## Notes
This master notebook serves as the reproducibility entry point for the complete analytical workflow.
